You've got
to be kidding me.

00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:25,236
I'm gonna go
and give you $100,000.

00:38:25,236 --> 00:38:26,671
I want 50%.

00:38:26,671 --> 00:38:28,840
♪♪

00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:30,475
[ Laughs ]

00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:32,110
You know why?

00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:33,845
'Cause you don't know
what you don't know.

00:38:33,845 --> 00:38:36,214
And you really need somebody
to actually endorse this

00:38:36,214 --> 00:38:37,448
and help you
get it out there.

00:38:37,448 --> 00:38:38,650
Yeah, but this ‐‐
this product solves a...

00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:40,318
Greiner: All right.
Hold on.

00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:42,387
I have some good news
and some bad news.

00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:44,489
What do you want first?

00:38:44,489 --> 00:38:47,292
♪♪

00:38:53,131 --> 00:38:55,266
Narrator:
Three Sharks are out.

00:38:55,266 --> 00:38:59,170
Kevin has made an offer
of $100,000 for a 50% stake

00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:02,707
of Alexander's wine‐cooling
product, ProntoBev.

00:39:02,707 --> 00:39:04,409
Greiner: All right.
Hold on.

00:39:04,409 --> 00:39:06,411
I have some good news
and some bad news.

00:39:06,411 --> 00:39:08,046
What do you want first?

00:39:08,046 --> 00:39:09,280
Give me the bad news first.

00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:11,082
Bad news first.
I'm out.

00:39:11,082 --> 00:39:13,284
[ Cuban laughs ]

00:39:14,652 --> 00:39:17,689
Lori! What's the good news
from that?

00:39:17,689 --> 00:39:19,591
I'll tell you
the good news.

00:39:19,591 --> 00:39:22,260
The good news is, I think
you have something clever.

00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:24,896
And I think
that it has merit.

00:39:24,896 --> 00:39:27,398
I went out because I think
that there's a lot

00:39:27,398 --> 00:39:30,602
of time and education
and learning and tweaking

00:39:30,602 --> 00:39:32,403
for you to get
to a price point

00:39:32,403 --> 00:39:34,272
that I think
will be a ‐‐ a hero.

00:39:34,272 --> 00:39:36,074
But I‐I do think...
Are you still out?

00:39:36,074 --> 00:39:37,642
...you have the potential
to get there

00:39:37,642 --> 00:39:39,177
and you have
a member of the...

00:39:39,177 --> 00:39:41,112
Chevaliers.
...Chevaliers du Tastevin!

00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:42,947
‐Oh!
‐Hey! Give me a refill.

00:39:42,947 --> 00:39:44,616
Now, listen.
Alexander, you do have an offer.

00:39:44,616 --> 00:39:45,650
What do you want to do?

00:39:45,650 --> 00:39:48,753
There's no way
I have any flexibility.

00:39:48,753 --> 00:39:50,421
I've been doing this
my whole life.

00:39:50,421 --> 00:39:52,757
Look ‐‐ Well ‐‐
Man, you can't give up
50% of your company, Alexander.

00:39:52,757 --> 00:39:54,225
‐I'm s‐‐ It's not a company!
‐But it's a ‐‐

00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,493
It's Alexander's discussion
with Kevin.

00:39:55,493 --> 00:39:57,729
Kevin, if ‐‐ if I gave you
50% of my company...

00:39:57,729 --> 00:39:59,631
O'Leary: Right.
...it would be doomed
from that moment.

00:39:59,631 --> 00:40:01,766
Why?
Because I need equity
to play around with

00:40:01,766 --> 00:40:03,468
so I can raise more money
if I need to.
I gave you 50%.

00:40:03,468 --> 00:40:04,602
50% is ‐‐ is not ‐‐

00:40:04,602 --> 00:40:06,738
Is there a better partner
than me?

00:40:06,738 --> 00:40:07,839
Is there?

00:40:07,839 --> 00:40:09,007
20%.
No!

00:40:09,007 --> 00:40:10,508
Are you...

00:40:10,508 --> 00:40:11,643
No.
No, no, no.

00:40:11,643 --> 00:40:14,145
I take you out of the
wastelands, the darkness.

00:40:14,145 --> 00:40:16,581
I bring you to the light.

00:40:16,581 --> 00:40:18,449
Darkness...light.
‐Oh, my.

00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:20,618
That's what's gonna happen.
That's what's going to happen.

00:40:20,618 --> 00:40:23,154
You have a high probability
of making money,

00:40:23,154 --> 00:40:26,524
versus you walk out the door
with ‐‐ without a deal.

00:40:26,524 --> 00:40:28,126
And you are so dead to me.

00:40:28,126 --> 00:40:29,861
I won't even remember
this thing.

00:40:29,861 --> 00:40:31,162
I'm willing to negotiate,

00:40:31,162 --> 00:40:32,797
but I need to keep some equity,
"A," for myself...

00:40:32,797 --> 00:40:34,465
You're right!
Yeah, don't be greedy.

00:40:34,465 --> 00:40:36,134
...'cause I should have
the majority...
That's Business School 101.

00:40:36,134 --> 00:40:38,303
...and, "B," so I can go
and raise the other $100,000.

00:40:38,303 --> 00:40:40,505
I have interested people
in the other $100,000.

00:40:40,505 --> 00:40:42,206
Look, if you had come
more advanced

00:40:42,206 --> 00:40:45,343
with sell‐through and proven
sales, that's different.

00:40:45,343 --> 00:40:46,477
I would have give you
more credit

00:40:46,477 --> 00:40:47,545
and maybe had flexibility.

00:40:47,545 --> 00:40:50,181
You have none of those things,
okay?

00:40:50,181 --> 00:40:51,816
Kevin,
are you stuck at the 50%?

00:40:51,816 --> 00:40:54,319
I said at the beginning, Robert,
I have no flexibility!

00:40:54,319 --> 00:40:56,587
Then give him $200,000
or $250,000.
No!

00:40:56,587 --> 00:40:57,822
Greiner: Yeah, give him
the extra $100,000 he needs.

00:40:57,822 --> 00:40:59,023
Look.
Simone:
How do I raise the money, Kevin?

00:40:59,023 --> 00:41:00,491
If you're gonna be my partner,
I ‐‐ This needs to happen.

00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:01,592
Where are I gonna get
the other $100,000?

00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:02,894
I get diluted, too.
So we all ‐‐

00:41:02,894 --> 00:41:04,128
Maybe I'll go in
on that route.

00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:05,930
Maybe I'll put more money
into it. But I'm starting ‐‐

00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:07,131
Yeah, now he owns
less than 50%.

00:41:07,131 --> 00:41:08,666
It's not his company anymore.
That's his point.

00:41:08,666 --> 00:41:10,702
Yeah. Then you're
gonna take more.
Cry me a river, Mark.

00:41:10,702 --> 00:41:12,370
Yes or no, Alexander?

00:41:12,370 --> 00:41:14,405
You won't budge at all?
O'Leary: None! Zero!

00:41:14,405 --> 00:41:15,440
'Cause you're giving me
no wriggle room here.

00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:18,109
It's binary ‐‐ yes or no.

00:41:18,109 --> 00:41:20,878
This is your moment.
You decide.

00:41:22,046 --> 00:41:23,948
What's your next product,
Alexander?

00:41:23,948 --> 00:41:25,316
Our next product
is a martini shaker...

00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:26,651
What are you talking
to him for? He's already out.

00:41:26,651 --> 00:41:28,386
...that ‐‐
that chills martinis.

00:41:28,386 --> 00:41:30,254
So ‐‐ So, you need...
You know, the problem
